Robot Arm Host Manifest
===============================================================================

The robot arm host manifest declares the provider and contexts exposed by the demo robot arm host.

1. Provider
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```text
robot-arm
```

2. Contexts
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```text
arm/commands
arm/state
```

The concrete instance name is chosen by project config. Examples often use an instance such as `arm`.

3. Operations
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Context | Operations |
|---------|------------|
| `commands` | `move`, `grip`, `home` |
| `state` | `read` |

4. Base URIs
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The materialized base URI shape is:

```text
robot://{instance}/commands
robot://{instance}/state
```
